      "role": "user",
      "content": "yo i just finished replacing the brake pads on my 2018 camry but now when i test drive it i get this really high pitched squealing noise when i hit the brakes. not sure if its a worn sensor or if i messed up the caliper or something. what should i check first?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Squealing brakes, especially after a pad change, is a common nuisance. You should check the brake pads and rotors first, as a new pad might be rubbing against something, or perhaps the new pad isn't seated perfectly. Sometimes, a little bit of grease or a piece of grit gets lodged between the pad and the caliper, and that's the culprit. It's a small thing, but a little bit of a sticky situation can turn into a big, noisy mess.",
