    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i checked the pads and they seem seated okay. i don't see any extra grit or grease issues though. the noise is really piercing, almost like a metal-on-metal screeching. could it be the caliper is stuck or maybe the wear sensor is just being annoying?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A piercing screech, like metal on metal, sounds like something more serious than just a little dust, which is a real sign you need to look closer. If the pads look fine and there's no obvious debris, the next thing to check is the caliper itself. Sometimes, a caliper can get slightly seized up, or maybe a retaining pin isn't fully seated, causing the pad to drag just a hair. That's a common problem, and it's usually a simple adjustment, but you'd need to get your hands dirty to check the hardware.",
