    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "yeah i'll try looking at the caliper pins next. i'm just worried because the sound is so weird and sudden. like it just starts screaming out of nowhere when i touch the pedal. i've never heard a car make a noise quite like this before, it's super unsettling.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That sudden, piercing scream is definitely unsettling, and you're right to be cautious. When a noise starts *suddenly* like that, it often points to something binding or catching immediately. Before you start fiddling with those caliper pins, just take a moment to look at the rotor surface itself. Sometimes, if the rotor isn't perfectly clean or if there's a slight warp, the new pad can catch on it in a very specific spot, causing that high-pitched shriek.\n\nIt's a bit of a gamble, but sometimes the issue isn't the pad or the caliper, but the metal surfaces themselves. Remember, even the smallest piece of rust or a tiny burr on the rotor can make a huge racket. If you're feeling nervous, maybe you should have a seasoned mechanic take a look. They've seen every kind of weird noise a car can make, and they can spot a problem faster than a frantic new-bie.",
      "source": "target",
